Battle of the Morcuera

865 battle as part of the Spanish Reconquista

0 0

2.

Emirate of Córdoba

Independent Islamic emirate in the Iberian Peninsula (756-929)

Overview: The Emirate of Córdoba (Arabic: إمارة قرطبة‎, Imārat Qurṭuba) was an independent emirate in the Iberian Peninsula ruled by the Umayyad dynasty with Córdoba as its capital.

0 0

3.

Haras (unit)

Personal bodyguards of the Caliphs

Overview: The haras (Arabic: الحرس; "the Guard") was a personal bodyguard unit of the caliphs during the Umayyads and the Abbasids. The haras was also instituted in the Emirate of Córdoba in present-day Spain.

0 0
